               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-267-person2491">
                  CHARLES 
                  READ
               <interp inst="t18200918-267-person2491" type="surname" value="READ"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-267-person2491" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-267-person2491" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18200918-267-viclabel1531" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-267-victim2490 t18200918-267-viclabel1531"></join>, and live in Newman-street. On the 9th of August, a little after eleven o'clock at night, I was at the corner of <placeName id="t18200918-267-crimeloc1532">George-street, St. Giles's</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-267-crimeloc1532" type="placeName" value="George-street, St. Giles's"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-267-crimeloc1532" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-267-off1529 t18200918-267-crimeloc1532"></join>, with two pair of trowsers in a bundle. I saw the prisoner and two others at the opposite corner; he crossed directly over to me, snatched the bundle from under my arm, and ran off with it - I followed, calling Stop thief! His companions crosed between us to hinder me, but I kept my eye on him - he ran away with a number of them. I was afraid to go in after him - he was stopped in a minute. My bundle was conveyed away. I am positive he is the man, for I did not lose sight of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-267-person2492">
                  LEWIS 
                  ROBERTS
               <interp inst="t18200918-267-person2492" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-267-person2492" type="given" value="LEWIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-267-person2492" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I heard the cry, saw a crowd running, and went in a direction to meet them, the prisoner was the foremost; I laid hold of him, Read appeared immediately, and said he was the man.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. If he saw me take it he can say what I did with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18200918-267-verdict1533" type="verdictDescription">
